# 🌍 AWS Route 53 Hands-On Project

## 📌 Overview

This project focuses on AWS Route 53, a scalable Domain Name System (DNS) web service provided by AWS.

The project demonstrates domain management, DNS routing, hosted zones, DNS records, and health checks used for reliable application networking.

---

# 🚀 Services Used

* AWS Route 53
* Amazon VPC
* EC2
* Public & Private Hosted Zones

---

# 🌐 What is Route 53?

Amazon Route 53 is a highly available and scalable DNS service used to route internet traffic to AWS resources and applications.

It helps users:

* Register domain names
* Manage DNS records
* Route traffic efficiently
* Monitor application health
* Configure public and private DNS

